external_knowledge:
- "precious gems" metaphorically refers to properties;
- "hosts who have a crown of at least two properties" means hosts managing more than one property;
- "praised by at least a dozen travelers" means the host has received more than 10 reviews in total across all their properties;
- "number of admirers" refers to the total number of reviews;
- "overall luster" refers to the average review rating;
- "richness of their features" refers to the number of amenities.

- 'gardeners' refers to hosts managing properties;
- 'plants' refers to properties;
- 'plot' refers to the number of listings managed by a host.

- "Prestigious neighbourhoods" refers to neighbourhoods with the highest average property prices;
- "Affordable gems" refers to the top 3 cheapest properties within each of the top 3 neighbourhoods;
- "Property types" include categories such as house, apartment, and condo.

- 'top-priced houses' refers to houses ranked among the top 3 most expensive in their respective neighborhoods;
- 'minimum stay of more than 30 nights' is a condition applied to the property listings;
- 'managing multiple properties' means the host has more than one property listed.

- "Highly reviewed and priced properties" refers to properties with a price greater than 50 and at least 5 reviews;
- "Shine brighter" is a metaphor for having higher average review ratings;
- "Overall property scene" refers to all properties in the neighborhood, including those with fewer reviews or lower prices.

- "Jewels of the neighborhood" refers to properties that stand out in their respective neighborhoods;
- "Average price of the properties managed by their hosts" is the average price of all properties managed by the same host;
- "Average price of properties in each neighborhood" is the average price of all properties within the same neighborhood.

- "top 10 properties" refers to the highest ranking properties based on the specified criteria;
- "average review ratings" are calculated by averaging the ratings from all reviews for each property;
- "most reviews" indicates the properties with the highest number of reviews;
- "highest total revenue" is the sum of the total prices paid for bookings of each property.

- "price per night that surpasses the $50 threshold" refers to properties where the price is greater than $50.00;
- "booking window of less than a week" refers to properties with a minimum number of nights required for booking less than 7;
- "shine brightly with the highest average review ratings" refers to properties with the highest average review ratings.

- "Guardians of the realm" refers to the hosts managing the properties;
- "Reputation scores" refers to the average review ratings;
- "Judged by the council of many (more than 10)" means the hosts have received more than 10 reviews;
- "Honored reputation" refers to the average review rating, with higher ratings being more esteemed.

- 'Entire home/apt' and 'Private room' refer to the types of rooms offered for rent;
- 'availability_365' of 200 days means the property is available for booking for at least 200 days in a year;
- 'number_of_reviews > 0' means the property has received at least one review.

- The `top 3 hosts` refers to the hosts with the highest number of properties managed;
- The `average review rating` is calculated by averaging the ratings of all properties managed by each host;
- The `total revenue` is the sum of the total prices for all bookings of the properties managed by each host.

- "Shining stars" refers to hosts with an average review rating greater than 4.5;
- "Consistently available" means the property is available for more than 300 days;
- "Budget-friendly price" refers to properties priced less than 100 per night;
- "Cozy entire home or apartment" means the property type and room type are both 'Entire home/apt'.

- "more reviews" refers to the total number of reviews being greater than the average total reviews across all hosts;
- "better average rating" refers to the average review rating being higher than the average review rating across all hosts;
- "manage more than one property" means the host has more than one listing.
